aiTopic: This workflow takes Illumina-sequenced ARTIC data, trims ARTIC primer sequences, identifies amplicons affected by ARTIC primer-binding site mutations and excludes tainted amplicons' reads for a variation analysis on ARTIC PE data.
This workflow takes a VCF dataset of COVID-19 variant sequences, applies filtering based on allele frequency and depth, and reports tabular lists of variants and an overview plot.
The workflow performs read mapping with minimap2 and variant calling with medaka for ARTIC data, sequenced by Oxford Nanopore Technologies, using ivar for primer trimming.
The workflow maps paired end reads with bwa-mem, performs sensitive variant calling across a wide range of AFs with lofreq, and processes COVID-19 WGS PE data.

The workflow generates a consensus sequence for COVID-19 by building intrasample variants, filtering variants based on allele-frequency, identifying regions with low coverage, and masking ambiguous sites.
The workflow annotates variants in SARS-CoV-2 Illumina sequencing data and classifies samples using pangolin and nextclade.
The workflow downloads fastq files for provided sequencing run accessions, splits the accessions for parallel processing, and extracts reads in FASTQ format.

The workflow is a RNA-Seq analysis pipeline configuration file which includes parameters for pipeline options, decoding, alignment, trimming, read counting, quality control, setting default parameters, calling different containers and capturing exit codes.

The BROAD Best Practice Data Pre-processing Workflow 4.1.0.0 prepares data for variant calling analysis, operating on individual samples, and includes alignment to reference genome and data cleanup operations.
The workflow processes VCF files into GDS files, assigns unique variant IDs and optionally checks the GDS files against the original VCF files.
The workflow processes 10x Genomics sequencing data, correcting cell barcodes and UMIs, aligning reads, marking duplicates, and returning data in BAM format and as counts in a sparse matrix format.
This workflow concatenates the content of columns from several files and stores the resultant file and versioning details.
The workflow converts BAM files into sorted and unmapped BAM files using Broad Institute's GATK software on the Google Cloud Platform.

The notebook demonstrates how to create interactive maps of US state tax data in a Jupyter notebook without writing JavaScript or Python code, using the libraries folium, xlrd, seaborn, pandas, and matplotlib.
The command line tool demonstrates an alternative descriptor to Dockstore.cwl, using a Docker container for the sort command shared with bamstats.
